<span id="freeTextContainer8063555762508515741">Terribly beautiful. I&apos;ve admired Grossman&apos;s work for years, but I&apos;ve felt that he always stopped short of exploring the full extent of the situations he describes, whether in his journalism or his fiction. This book shatters the glass wall and at times it was so painful to read that I had to put it down, but everything was rendered so exquisitely that I had to keep reading.</span>
  <span id="freeText8063555762508515741" style="display:none">Terribly beautiful. I've admired Grossman's work for years, but I've felt that he always stopped short of exploring the full extent of the situations he describes, whether in his journalism or his fiction. This book shatters the glass wall and at times it was so painful to read that I had to put it down, but everything was rendered so exquisitely that I had to keep reading.</span>
