<div id="review_3393924812" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3393924812" />
    <a title="Tundra" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43990165-tundra"><img alt="Tundra" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609448117p2/43990165.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3393924812?book_show_action=true">Jul 04, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tundra" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tundra" href="/user/show/43990165-tundra">Tundra</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780224089999" href="/book/show/8432292-to-the-end-of-the-land">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3393924812" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5356275733333229829">I don’t know where to begin with this book because there is so much to explore and think about. It’s emotionally extremely intense and after the first half I progressed in small chunks. Ora, Avram and Ofer have a complex inter-relationship of love, friendship and guilt. Their lives are completely entwined in a way that has them permanently dependent on each other but also unable to bear each other’s company. <br/><br/>The section of the book where we relive Avram awaiting capture is heartbreaking. It is e</span>
  <span id="freeText5356275733333229829" style="display:none">I don’t know where to begin with this book because there is so much to explore and think about. It’s emotionally extremely intense and after the first half I progressed in small chunks. Ora, Avram and Ofer have a complex inter-relationship of love, friendship and guilt. Their lives are completely entwined in a way that has them permanently dependent on each other but also unable to bear each other’s company. <br /><br />The section of the book where we relive Avram awaiting capture is heartbreaking. It is easy to imagine why Ora has taken herself away from home to hide from any news while her son serves his final military service. <br /><br />I also thought about the senseless of war and the impact of this on families and individuals. Each valley, mountain or monument that is inscribed with a memorial to a lost child wears away at your hope that this will ever end. The unfairness and suspicion with which the Palestinians are treated and how everyone appears to shut down their emotional intelligence in order to live through another day is harrowing.<br /><br />This is definitely a book that is worth reading but only if you are prepared to put in the time.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5356275733333229829" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


